description:
src/signatures.rs:63-80 — verify_signature builds the signed string with a push-loop:

    let mut lines = Vec::new();
    for h in signed_headers {
        if h == "(request-target)" {
            lines.push(format!(...));
        } else {
            ...
            lines.push(format!("{h}: {val}"));
        }
    }
    let signed_string = lines.join("\n");

This could be expressed as a map+collect with fallible iterator (.try_fold or map returning Result + collect::<Result<Vec<_>, _>>()), which would also allow early ? return for the missing-header error instead of the current with_context inside the loop.

Impact: Readability/idiom. The loop makes the flow harder to follow and prevents the function from being expressed as a pipeline.
